This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with the evaluation of semantic models and lexical entailment, which are important topics in NLP. It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the performance of state-of-the-art models. Additionally, it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with human-like cognitive processes such as category membership. The paper also involves crowdsourcing, which could place it under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of improved graded LE systems, which could place it under Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
